The paper deals with supporting continuous queries over large, dynamic graphs, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The focus on aggregate queries and the use of pre-computed data structures suggests a potential fit with topics in social networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The need for low latency and high throughput also suggests a potential fit with systems and control (cs.SY) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
